## Chat-V2 Blocker Resolution
**Status:** draft

| Chat-V2 Issue | Status | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| #1 BLOCKER: URL mismatch `/sessions/all` vs `/sessions` | **RESOLVED** | Frontend uses `${API_BASE}/sessions` (line 59), backend registers `.route("/api/forge/chats/sessions", ...delete(...))`. `sessions/all` does NOT exist anywhere in `frontend/src`. Previous reviewer analyzed stale code. |

### Criterion Assessment
| Goal/Spec | Status | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| Chat-G10: Delete all в†’ create blank session | вњ… pass | Backend clears store, creates new `ForgeSession`, returns `DeleteAllSessionsResponse` with `deleted_count`, `new_session_id`, `session` |
| Chat-G10: Network/cancel errors preserve sessions | вњ… pass | Frontend try/catch/finally sets `_error`, re-throws, resets `_isLoading` in finally |
| Chat-A1: DELETE endpoint response shape | вњ… pass | `DeleteAllSessionsResponse` matches spec: `deleted_count: usize`, `new_session_id: String`, `session: ForgeSessionSummary` |
| Chat-A1: URL consistency frontend в†” backend | вњ… pass | Both use `DELETE /api/forge/chats/sessions` |
| Chat-D1: ConfirmDialog + loading state | вњ… pass | `_isLoading` ref controls UI state, `hasSessions` computed guards button |

### Static Analysis
| Check | Status | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Type signatures match spec | вњ… pass | Response struct fields match Chat-A1 exactly |
| Error handling вЂ” frontend | вњ… pass | try/catch/finally with `_error` and `_isLoading` reset |
| Error handling вЂ” backend | вљ пёЏ partial | `lock().unwrap()` on mutex вЂ” acceptable for single-threaded Axum state, but panics on poison |
| No dead code in useSessions.ts | вњ… pass | All exports used: `sessionList`, `isLoading`, `error`, `sessionCount`, `hasSessions`, `loadSessionList`, `deleteSession`, `deleteAllSessions` |
| Security вЂ” auth enforcement | вљ пёЏ partial | Frontend uses `authFetch` (sends JWT). Backend route has no explicit auth middleware visible in route chain. However, Axum layer middleware may apply globally. Needs confirmation. |

### Remaining Issues (Non-Blocking)

| # | Severity | Description | Recommendation | Assignee |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | major | Backend `delete_all_forge_sessions()` operates on in-memory `forge_sessions()` store only. `session::delete_all_sessions()` in `session.rs` operates on filesystem. Two implementations are disconnected вЂ” the route handler never calls the filesystem function. If sessions persist to disk, deleting from memory won't clear disk. | Unify: route handler should call `session::delete_all_sessions()` or architecture should document in-memory-only design. | Coder |
| 2 | minor | No integration test exists that verifies frontendв†’backend end-to-end for delete-all. Frontend mocks `fetch`, backend tests exercise filesystem function only. The two code paths are never tested together. | Add a route-level integration test that calls the handler and verifies store state. | Coder |
| 3 | minor | Backend `lock().unwrap()` will panic on poisoned mutex. In production, if another handler panics while holding the lock, all subsequent delete-all requests will panic. | Use `lock().unwrap_or_else(|e| e.into_inner())` or return `StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR`. | Coder |

